		<dateModified>Fri, 13 Aug 2021 18:29:16 GMT</dateModified>
		<urlInstant>http://instantoutliner.com/qe</urlInstant>
		</head>
	<body>
		<outline text="August 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="august2021" >
			<outline text="August 13" type="calendarDay" name="13" >
				<outline text="The Co-Founder Of The Fact-Checking Site Snopes Wrote Plagiarized Articles Under A Fake Name &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/deansterlingjones/snopes-cofounder-plagiarism-mikkelson&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; And did other things that are totally unethical." type="tweet" created="Fri, 13 Aug 2021 18:28:45 GMT" tweetId="1426249379195785227" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1426249379195785227" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Greatly enjoyed this thread by computer security expert @ErrataRob about Mike Pillow's proof event. Pillow Guy said he has &quot;packet captures&quot; that show election fraud. He asked real experts to come and see the proof. Twice I had to stop because I broke down laughing. Final score: &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ErrataRob/status/1425913689169928192&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 13 Aug 2021 15:29:46 GMT" tweetId="1426204337685028869" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1426204337685028869" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 12" type="calendarDay" name="12" >
				<outline text="Major newspaper chan is revamping its approach to crime coverage. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.poynter.org/reporting-editing/2021/gannett-launches-a-network-wide-push-to-rework-its-crime-coverage/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; I read this with two reactions:

1. &quot;This is smart, I'm glad their fixing that...&quot;

2. But my god, it's been broken like this for generations. The critiques were made, the research was done." type="tweet" created="Thu, 12 Aug 2021 16:54:27 GMT" tweetId="1425863262156070912" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1425863262156070912" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 11" type="calendarDay" name="11" >
				<outline text="&quot;If your website is full of assholes, itâs your fault.&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://medium.com/humane-tech/the-immortal-myths-about-online-abuse-a156e3370aee&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 18:21:49 GMT" tweetId="1425522858407698433" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1425522858407698433" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="It has virtues, too, but CNN's vice has always been entertainment. The maudlin, the sentimental, the news family with vivid characters eclipsing the news team with high standards.

With the Cuomos, Jeff Zucker chose family melodrama over journalism logic.  &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/10/business/media/chris-cuomo-cnn-andrew-cuomo.html%20&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 16:36:52 GMT" tweetId="1425496448171401220" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1425496448171401220" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="This surprises me. The top editor of the @postandcourier in Charleston, SC, family-owned and on the rise nationally, is taking the top job at the Chicago Tribune, bleeding talent in the grip of Alden Global Capital, the crocodile hedge fund. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.postandcourier.com/news/post-and-courier-s-mitch-pugh-named-editor-in-chief-of-chicago-tribune/article_347b61ba-f9de-11eb-a198-4f397b5cd810.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 15:23:53 GMT" tweetId="1425478080370462722" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1425478080370462722" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 10" type="calendarDay" name="10" >
				<outline text="Perry is rapdily becoming our most useful political columnist. Here he explains why it's lazy and wrong to claim that &quot;moderates&quot; or &quot;centrists&quot; hold the key to winning elections and passing legislation.  &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/2021/08/09/why-moderation-doesnt-guarantee-electoral-success-biden-democrats/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; Recommended. @perrybaconjr" type="tweet" created="Tue, 10 Aug 2021 18:43:16 GMT" tweetId="1425165868712009728" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1425165868712009728" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 5" type="calendarDay" name="05" >
				<outline text="One way you know that Fox is not a NEWS network is that the star of a genuine news network would not anchor his show from the capital of democracy's blackslide, where an independent press is being squeezed out, unless he wanted to warn his viewers that this could happen to them. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/NewDay/status/1422897249533652992&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 17:16:40 GMT" tweetId="1423332138812854272" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1423332138812854272" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 4" type="calendarDay" name="04" >
				<outline text="Documenters is a nonprofit that pays community members to take notes (and often live tweet) at public meetingsâ like school boards. The notes are then posted on the Documenters website, where they are publicly viewable and searchable. &lt;a href=&quot;https://kappanonline.org/walker-in-cleveland-community-efforts-fill-in-for-school-coverage-russo/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 04 Aug 2021 19:21:13 GMT" tweetId="1423001093219495939" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1423001093219495939" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="New entrant. Puck News says its &quot;reinventing the business model&quot; in journalism, &quot;in partnership with the journalists themselves,&quot; and that it is &quot;focused on the inside story at the nexus of Hollywood, Wall Street, Washington, and Silicon Valley.&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://puck.news/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 04 Aug 2021 17:07:01 GMT" tweetId="1422967320939483139" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1422967320939483139" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 3" type="calendarDay" name="03" >
				<outline text="The second day of @membershippzzle's wrap-up summit on membership models in journalism. Just started. You can find the full agenda and registration info here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://membershippuzzle.org/summit/agenda&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/zkERLki3LO" type="tweet" created="Tue, 03 Aug 2021 13:07:48 GMT" tweetId="1422544731482083328" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1422544731482083328" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 1" type="calendarDay" name="01" >
				<outline text="I give you this tight paragraph by George Packer in his latest book. He's writing about the spring and summer of 2020 and what the pandemic did to American democracy. Rarely do you see experts, politicians and citizens put into proper standing like this. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1421946414498725897/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 01 Aug 2021 21:30:18 GMT" tweetId="1421946414498725897" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1421946414498725897" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			</outline>
		<outline text="July 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="july2021" >
			<outline text="July 31" type="calendarDay" name="31" >
				<outline text="From my blog, PressThink, 17 years ago. https://t.co/vOaUnlMIaM https://t.co/JhGKR5arYk" type="tweet" created="Sun, 01 Aug 2021 02:09:01 GMT" tweetId="1421654170491310085" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1421654170491310085" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 30" type="calendarDay" name="30" >
				<outline text="Next week, the research project I direct, @membershippzzle, will be holding its wrap-up event, a summit on the spread of membership models in public service journalism. It's online. It's free. It's global. Half days, August 2-6.

Registration and schedule: &lt;a href=&quot;https://membershippuzzle.org/summit/agenda&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 19:26:29 GMT" tweetId="1421190481883680770" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1421190481883680770" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="There was additional news today on the investors in this venture. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cnbc.com/2021/07/30/tech-exec-invests-in-digital-news-startup-launched-by-veteran-journalists.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/XTTsQ2V5e6" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 18:04:09 GMT" tweetId="1421169758683254793" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1421169758683254793" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 29" type="calendarDay" name="29" >
				<outline text="Jim Jordan is asked if he talked to Trump on Jan. 6. His system goes mildly haywire, sputtering to a halt around a different fact: that he talks to the president all the time. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/Acyn/status/1420147017242746885/video/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; Eventually he admits that he did talk to POTUS, yes.

Then two days later... 1/2" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 00:05:43 GMT" tweetId="1420898365412368384" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1420898365412368384" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="You may not be a part of a movement and practice professional detachment â in a good way â but find yourself marching anyhow. I think we're headed for just that. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/AdamSerwer/status/1420808870654586880&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 29 Jul 2021 19:23:56 GMT" tweetId="1420827449353457667" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1420827449353457667" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="NPR's ethics policy used to claim the right to prevent its newsroom people from joining in a march or rally for any controversial cause, even if it had nothing to do with the reporter's beat or the journalist's work. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.npr.org/sections/publiceditor/2021/07/29/1021802098/new-npr-ethics-policy-its-ok-for-journalists-to-demonstrate-sometimes&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; It's been changed. Now it says this.... https://t.co/2vAIFD6yxZ" type="tweet" created="Thu, 29 Jul 2021 17:17:20 GMT" tweetId="1420795592251482119" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1420795592251482119" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="At UNC, they're asking: how did a statement of values identified with rich alum Walter Hussman become the J-school's principles, such that they were to be â quite literally â etched in stone at Chapel Hill? &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.ncpolicywatch.com/2021/07/28/unc-journalism-faculty-members-wealthy-donors-should-not-define-the-schools-values/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; My answer: they presented as journalism pieties." type="tweet" created="Thu, 29 Jul 2021 16:16:53 GMT" tweetId="1420780376176435210" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1420780376176435210" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 28" type="calendarDay" name="28" >
				<outline text="Always of interest when the savvier-than-you-are press cannot agree on whoâs playing higher chess. Last week âthe politics of thisâ were (according to The Savvy) that Pelosi created a bad look for herself by rejecting Jim Jordan and thus wrecking the appearance of bipartisanship. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/deadlinewh/status/1420522162071408641&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 28 Jul 2021 23:45:19 GMT" tweetId="1420530842376491013" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1420530842376491013" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="This system has failed. Both sides has been a bust. Working the refs works. The right wing mobilizes off charges of media bias. Resenting the press is basic to Republican identity, a core value. Conservative media thrives on lowering social trust and flooding the zone with crap. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/oliverdarcy/status/1420473960781783045&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 28 Jul 2021 22:29:19 GMT" tweetId="1420511716178374657" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1420511716178374657" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="One way you know Fox is not a NEWS network is that its standard is not, &quot;extraordinary claims require extraordinary evidence.&quot; Extraordinary claims can be launched on almost no evidence. The so-called &quot;news side&quot; of the operation will shrug and stand down. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/2021/07/27/tucker-carlson-nsa-story-bogus/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 28 Jul 2021 18:14:46 GMT" tweetId="1420447655218585603" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1420447655218585603" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="In her new column, @sulliview calls for leading news organizations to &quot;radically reframe the mission&quot; of Washington journalism â from game coverage to the defense of democracy â and to &quot;pull together their braintrusts&quot; to determine how this can be done. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/media/journalist-both-sides-politics-trump/2021/07/27/c3afd1f8-eee0-11eb-81d2-ffae0f931b8f_story.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 28 Jul 2021 14:56:25 GMT" tweetId="1420397741516132352" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1420397741516132352" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Here's a new column about this (old) idea: a problem solving lens can land you in a different place. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.patheos.com/blogs/slacktivist/2021/07/27/what-if-life-wasnt-just-a-zero-sum-game/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/rjl9rqLyk3" type="tweet" created="Wed, 28 Jul 2021 14:32:06 GMT" tweetId="1420391620411891719" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1420391620411891719" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 27" type="calendarDay" name="27" >
				<outline text="The New York Times published a story about this dilemma today. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/27/us/politics/trump-false-claims-media.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; &quot;Should news outlets contextualize false claims made by powerful people? Or ignore them completely? There is no consensus in the industry, but its thinking continues to evolve.&quot; https://t.co/LcsU2Eqwr2" type="tweet" created="Wed, 28 Jul 2021 00:49:27 GMT" tweetId="1420184591521009667" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1420184591521009667" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="@kimmasters Enjoyed watching you in Ronan's HBO thing." type="tweet" created="Tue, 27 Jul 2021 22:58:58 GMT" tweetId="1420156789350453249" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1420156789350453249" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Chuck Todd: &quot;We should have fought back better in the mainstream media. We shouldnât [have] accepted the premise that there was liberal bias... We bought into the idea that, oh my God, weâre perceived as having a liberal bias.&quot; 

From a new interview:  &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theverge.com/22594290/chuck-todd-meet-the-press-decoder-interview-nbc-news&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 27 Jul 2021 15:11:39 GMT" tweetId="1420039183515758601" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1420039183515758601" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" >
					<outline text="Todd has done this before. He admits that he and his colleagues should have recognized Republican tactics long ago, but he does not pledge to make any structural changes in his approach. This is from my post, &quot;The Christmas Even Confessions of Chuck Todd.&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://pressthink.org/2019/12/the-christmas-eve-confessions-of-chuck-todd/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/bx3R45iQLu" type="tweet" created="Tue, 27 Jul 2021 16:23:32 GMT" tweetId="1420057275109187585" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1420057275109187585" inReplyToId="1420039183515758601" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Most big American newspaper newsrooms are now led by someone other than a white man. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.niemanlab.org/2021/07/small-steps-but-most-big-american-newspaper-newsrooms-are-now-led-by-someone-other-than-a-white-man/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 27 Jul 2021 14:31:09 GMT" tweetId="1420028992455852044" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1420028992455852044" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 26" type="calendarDay" name="26" >
				<outline text="If you have not read it yet, this is a necessary thread. Its author is exasperatedâ for good reason. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/brianbeutler/status/1417896636085424129&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 26 Jul 2021 21:47:45 GMT" tweetId="1419776480108761106" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1419776480108761106" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="&quot;I never, ever, ever wanted to own a newspaper. Except that newspaper.&quot;

There's a small trend of local newspapers moving from the big chains and hedge funds into the hands of local investors who, of course, have entirely different motives for owning them. &lt;a href=&quot;https://localnewsinitiative.northwestern.edu/posts/2021/07/26/increasing-local-ownership/index.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 26 Jul 2021 21:39:32 GMT" tweetId="1419774412530888705" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1419774412530888705" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Not recent. More like a relic from an earlier era in American politics and media. 

You can treat the reflexive demand for bipartisanship as &quot;identity politics for media people,&quot; a way to separate their professional selves from what political scientists call &quot;policy demanders.&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/BBurner47/status/1419700697411555328&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 26 Jul 2021 17:01:47 GMT" tweetId="1419704512659533825" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1419704512659533825" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Melting into mush again over the demand for &quot;bipartisanship,&quot; the political press gave one of its most miserable performances since inauguration. This column in @CJR, &quot;The absurd coverage of the January 6 committee&quot; captures well the events of July 21-22. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cjr.org/the_media_today/january_6_committee_pelosi_media_bothsides_bipartisan.php&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 26 Jul 2021 16:40:06 GMT" tweetId="1419699056130109440" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1419699056130109440" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 25" type="calendarDay" name="25" >
				<outline text="Best thread I have read in months. A model for scholars seeking to adapt social science to social media. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ebharrington/status/1418281619312586755&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 25 Jul 2021 22:21:55 GMT" tweetId="1419422690155409410" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1419422690155409410" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="For &quot;deep wounds&quot; substitute &quot;politicized rage.&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/whstancil/status/1419273013506285568/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; Via @whstancil" type="tweet" created="Sun, 25 Jul 2021 15:09:57 GMT" tweetId="1419313983660728325" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1419313983660728325" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 23" type="calendarDay" name="23" >
				<outline text="I really like this turn from the @latimes. (Don't @ me with &quot;it's not new.&quot; Thanks. ð) &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/meridak/status/1418286025256755204&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 23 Jul 2021 19:29:14 GMT" tweetId="1418654456984608771" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1418654456984608771" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Good day to re-up this. A while back someone on Twitter asked me for three or four changes in political journalism that might begin to right this ship. (Emphasis on &quot;begin to...&quot;) Here is what I came up with. &lt;a href=&quot;https://pressthink.org/2020/09/you-might-not-like-it-but-its-smart-politics/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;  https://t.co/m462CLeEAt" type="tweet" created="Fri, 23 Jul 2021 19:20:29 GMT" tweetId="1418652256338067463" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1418652256338067463" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 22" type="calendarDay" name="22" >
				<outline text="Politico's Playbook: Adding Jim Jordon to the investigation makes the results harder to dismiss for people who arenât Team Blue. I see how this works for people who are reporters. For everyone else: how does successfully sown chaos become MORE convincing? &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.politico.com/newsletters/playbook/2021/07/22/return-of-the-masks-493689&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/wpoGi9G1P2" type="tweet" created="Thu, 22 Jul 2021 17:46:09 GMT" tweetId="1418266125641601027" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1418266125641601027" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Excellent questions, Greg. &quot;What would it take to make it credible to the GOP?&quot; and... &quot;Are these defensible demands?&quot; The banality of bipartisanship would be harder to sustain if the insider press had to begin that way. Read his thread. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ThePlumLineGS/status/1418226531042725888&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 22 Jul 2021 16:34:11 GMT" tweetId="1418248016792887297" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1418248016792887297" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="I always read job descriptions for the little hints they provide about a shifting industry, and the way the bosses are thinking about the workersâ and the work. &lt;a href=&quot;https://nbcnewsdigitaljobs.com/work-here&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/tOgq63O6zW" type="tweet" created="Thu, 22 Jul 2021 16:18:52 GMT" tweetId="1418244160138665984" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1418244160138665984" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 21" type="calendarDay" name="21" >
				<outline text="There are some stories â and this is one â that reveal the political press, rather than the other way around. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/timodc/status/1417942412798746624&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 21 Jul 2021 21:08:59 GMT" tweetId="1417954784510873607" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1417954784510873607" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="This is why I keep returning to critiques of the savvy style. It allows the writers of political news to bracket questions of truth and default to analysis of the game.
 
Thread. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/tzimmer_history/status/1417917352985907201&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 21 Jul 2021 20:39:10 GMT" tweetId="1417947278829105164" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1417947278829105164" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="I like how @chrislhayes put it. Fox show hosts are not so much anti-vax as anti pro-vax. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.mediaite.com/tv/chris-hayes-rips-cowardly-fox-news-hosts-for-vaccine-commentary-nihilistic-cynicism-and-preening-idiocy/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 21 Jul 2021 18:29:48 GMT" tweetId="1417914723006308354" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1417914723006308354" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="&quot;Why arenât conservatives pounding away that it was their guy who started the development of the vaccine under his overstated moniker Operation Warp Speed?&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/media/right-wing-media-vaccines-coronavirus/2021/07/20/b74befd2-e963-11eb-8950-d73b3e93ff7f_story.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;

There are answers to this, but it's a good question. By @Sulliview" type="tweet" created="Wed, 21 Jul 2021 17:38:51 GMT" tweetId="1417901902096969728" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1417901902096969728" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="What Zeleny is saying makes no sense to me. Ditto for his way of reporting it. No one on Biden's team thought this was either probable or possible? If true, that's malpractice. It also means Ron Klain is a fool, with a child-like grasp of politics. And that should be the story. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/brianstelter/status/1417870724484698113&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 21 Jul 2021 16:25:58 GMT" tweetId="1417883558778220551" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1417883558778220551" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 20" type="calendarDay" name="20" >
				<outline text="Not just further to the right, but further from the real. That's the direction in which the GOP is moving. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/RonBrownstein/status/1417607206841700354&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 20 Jul 2021 23:04:18 GMT" tweetId="1417621414723604484" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1417621414723604484" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Polling industry task force reports back: Election polls in 2020 produced an &quot;error of an unusual magnitude,&quot; and we are unable to say why. &lt;a href=&quot;https://theconversation.com/election-polls-in-2020-produced-error-of-unusual-magnitude-expert-panel-finds-without-pinpointing-cause-164759&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 20 Jul 2021 21:48:48 GMT" tweetId="1417602417886175238" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1417602417886175238" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Never occurs to these guys that fronting with free speech, open debate, no cancel culture, &quot;we're not biased like THEY are...&quot; creates problems for you when your actual intention is right wing support system. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cjr.org/the_media_today/gb_news_british_fox_nigel_farage.php&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;

Read how this unfolded at @GBNEWS in the UK." type="tweet" created="Tue, 20 Jul 2021 18:56:02 GMT" tweetId="1417558937197494280" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1417558937197494280" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Rather than an elite manufacturing consent, the propaganda model best suited to 21st century media is the âmanufacture of dissent.â &lt;a href=&quot;https://theconversation.com/we-are-all-propagandists-now-164519&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; Its goal is to involve everyone in disabling the public sphere, sowing chaos so no one knows whom to trust or what is true." type="tweet" created="Tue, 20 Jul 2021 17:41:38 GMT" tweetId="1417540213526700034" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1417540213526700034" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="To investigate and reveal the cover-up has been part of the mythology of journalism since Watergate. But in its classic form the cover-up is itself secret, setting the stage for the big reveal. The GOP's attempt to cover-up Jan. 6 is happening in public. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/2021/07/20/jim-banks-jan-6-committee-sabotage/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 20 Jul 2021 16:54:57 GMT" tweetId="1417528464668770307" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1417528464668770307" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 19" type="calendarDay" name="19" >
				<outline text="New CEO: &quot;My vision is for us to be the leading newsroom in America in equipping and inspiring change makers with our investigative journalism to reverse the effects of inequalities.&quot;

Long way from the view from nowhere. &lt;a href=&quot;https://publicintegrity.org/inside-publici/qa-paul-cheung-public-integrity-ceo-who-is-journalism-really-serving&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 20 Jul 2021 01:42:36 GMT" tweetId="1417298867184410626" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1417298867184410626" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="&quot;Tell me where you think I made a factual error. Iâm always glad to correct a factual error. If youâre just upset because I let you know what was going on in my head when I was news gathering, then, I mean thatâs a problem for your psychiatrist or priest.&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.elon.edu/u/nclnw/2021/07/14/joe-killian-of-nc-policy-watch-talks-about-nikole-hannah-jones-unc-the-art-of-reporting-fairness-and-the-faults-of-journalism/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 19 Jul 2021 13:50:53 GMT" tweetId="1417119757942366208" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1417119757942366208" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 18" type="calendarDay" name="18" >
				<outline text="I have been listening to this investigative podcast by the journalist @VickyPJWard. It's about Epstein and Ghislaine Maxwell. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.audible.com/pd/Prologue-Episode-1-Ghislaine-Behind-Bars-Podcast/B0988964P2&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;

Yes, I'm hooked. Mainly because I feel that by listening I am finally getting somewhere in the mystery of how he made his money." type="tweet" created="Mon, 19 Jul 2021 02:10:12 GMT" tweetId="1416943424637476867" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1416943424637476867" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Why People Are So Awful Online is a good column by @rgay. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/17/opinion/culture/social-media-cancel-culture-roxane-gay.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; 

I have been posting a lot less lately, in part because I feel boxed in by my own effort to anticipate â and prevent â the misunderstandings that are about to fly. (See next slide.) 1/2" type="tweet" created="Mon, 19 Jul 2021 01:29:26 GMT" tweetId="1416933163583090693" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1416933163583090693" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="A view-from-somewhere front page. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/brianstelter/status/1416729111402356740/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; Via @brianstelter" type="tweet" created="Sun, 18 Jul 2021 18:33:12 GMT" tweetId="1416828416347750408" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1416828416347750408" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="New British TV channel, @GBNEWS, which was supposed to be a more conservative alternative, recorded ZERO viewers for parts of the day after a viewer boycott prompted by one of its presenters taking the knee in solidarity with the England football team. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/media/2021/jul/15/gb-news-shows-attracted-zero-viewers-after-boycott-over-taking-the-knee&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 18 Jul 2021 17:25:15 GMT" tweetId="1416811317432832004" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1416811317432832004" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Anticipating a chance to put to him some questions, a journalist I know asked me what would I ask Chuck Todd. This was my answer. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1416778376812105739/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 18 Jul 2021 15:14:22 GMT" tweetId="1416778376812105739" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1416778376812105739" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 17" type="calendarDay" name="17" >
				<outline text="The words of @NicolleDWallace, who worked for a Republican White House and in two GOP campaigns. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.msnbc.com/msnbc/i-served-gop-20-years-demise-democracy-doesn-t-have-n1273773&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/Tdy7Snpkfn" type="tweet" created="Sun, 18 Jul 2021 02:16:54 GMT" tweetId="1416582721669935104" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1416582721669935104" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 16" type="calendarDay" name="16" >
				<outline text="Something @brianstelter said at the end of his most recent podcast with @davidfrum. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cnn.com/audio/podcasts/reliable-sources?episodeguid=cd3fae31-3fec-4782-89e9-ad660157f9a3&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/meM7fc7TZB" type="tweet" created="Fri, 16 Jul 2021 23:49:21 GMT" tweetId="1416183202994065410" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1416183202994065410" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="For my Brazilian friends, followers, and students. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/membershippzzle/status/1416046245605519361&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 16 Jul 2021 14:57:17 GMT" tweetId="1416049303752224768" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1416049303752224768" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 15" type="calendarDay" name="15" >
				<outline text="If I had to give the entire file of Trump coverage grades, there would be some As, Bs, Cs, Ds, and Fs for different streams in it. For the Ivanka Trump portion I would have to send a note home, &quot;please make an appointment to see me.&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2021/07/15/jan-6-i-alone-can-fix-it-book-excerpt/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;

This is about Jan. 6: https://t.co/cnqmmmxTTC" type="tweet" created="Fri, 16 Jul 2021 00:14:40 GMT" tweetId="1415827184011329536" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1415827184011329536" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" >
					<outline text="It never stops. She's always trying to do the right thing, as the right thing fails to gets done. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2021/07/15/jan-6-i-alone-can-fix-it-book-excerpt/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/CE5fzPWKsD" type="tweet" created="Fri, 16 Jul 2021 14:27:17 GMT" tweetId="1416041755187818507" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1416041755187818507" inReplyToId="1415827184011329536" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="&quot;He sanitizes and legitimizes right-wing conspiratorial thinking, dodges when you try to nail him down on the specifics, then wraps it all in an argument about censorship and free speech...&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://time.com/6080432/tucker-carlson-profile/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;

I read all the Tucker Carlson profiles. None quite gets there." type="tweet" created="Thu, 15 Jul 2021 19:03:10 GMT" tweetId="1415748792960397316" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1415748792960397316" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Enjoy reading about toweringly stupid culture war products dreamed up and launched up by the Murdoch forces with the most vapid hype attached, then quietly dropped years later because they never had a prayer of working? Well... @NiemanLab has you covered. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.niemanlab.org/2021/07/i-have-to-come-to-bury-knewz-not-to-praise-it/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 15 Jul 2021 16:03:47 GMT" tweetId="1415703651830673410" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1415703651830673410" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 14" type="calendarDay" name="14" >
				<outline text="Read @daveweigel on being &quot;based&quot; vs. being &quot;cringe&quot; in politics.  &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2021/07/13/trailer-based-or-cringe-new-way-explaining-same-old-political-brawls/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; Briefly: An appeal to norms and fairness is &quot;cringe&quot; behavior. Breaking rules to get what you see as right is &quot;based.&quot;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 21:01:44 GMT" tweetId="1415416246007472133" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1415416246007472133" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="The press cannot return to its posture as as disinterested or neutral, writes @perrybaconjr. &quot;Nor should it if Trump and Trumpism remain threats to democracy. It needs to chart a new path forward for a United States with a Trumpian Republican Party.&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/2021/07/12/media-must-reinvent-itself-era-trumpian-politics-heres-how/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;

Yes." type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 17:01:09 GMT" tweetId="1415355699840921604" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1415355699840921604" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="The research project I direct, @membershippzzle, is coming to a close in August. We're going out big, with a summit examining the state of membership models in journalism world wide. It's free, online, half days, August 2-6. We just published the schedule. &lt;a href=&quot;https://membershippuzzle.org/summit/agenda&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 15:41:52 GMT" tweetId="1415335748140736514" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1415335748140736514" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="What's your new show about, Shep?
â News
News of what?
â Important news
What's the focus?
â News, not talk
Any particular lens?
â The lens is news
Who's it for?
â Everyone who wants news
Why would I watch?
â Because we're good at doing news

&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.thedailybeast.com/inside-shepard-smiths-post-fox-news-crash-on-cnbc&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 15:17:12 GMT" tweetId="1415329538335256580" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1415329538335256580" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 13" type="calendarDay" name="13" >
				<outline text="This is much the case for the term &quot;objectivity&quot; in journalism. It means at least 25 things, and when we argue about it we are almost never grabbing hold of the same object. Which is why the arguments never go anywhere. &lt;a href=&quot;https://warzel.substack.com/p/how-to-have-difficult-conversations&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; And why &quot;bias&quot; fills the gap. https://t.co/HP0c0IAqDf" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 03:22:34 GMT" tweetId="1415149696335716354" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1415149696335716354" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Increasingly I find myself in need of a button that would turn off replies seeking to inform me that what I have said is not new, when I have made no such claim and would not dream of it. And yes, I know I sound like a crank, which is all the more reason I need this feature NOW. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TwitterSafety/status/1415025551773892608&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 02:46:02 GMT" tweetId="1415140502400290817" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1415140502400290817" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Pew: In 2020 the average prime time audience increased by 61% for Fox to about 3.08 million, compared with 1.92 million in 2019. CNN rose 72% from 1.05 million in 2019 to 1.80 million in 2020. MSNBC rose 28% from 1.3 million in 2019 to 1.6 million in 2020. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.journalism.org/fact-sheet/cable-news/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 13 Jul 2021 19:36:46 GMT" tweetId="1415032474070044674" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1415032474070044674" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="The journalist's affection for colorful characters who give off memorable quotes and politicians who are open about their corruption â rather than sanctimonious and staid â is readable right off the surface of this obit. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/12/us/politics/edwin-edwards-dead.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; No decoding necessary." type="tweet" created="Tue, 13 Jul 2021 15:13:49 GMT" tweetId="1414966298648498182" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1414966298648498182" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 12" type="calendarDay" name="12" >
				<outline text="&quot;A two-party lens is the only way the news media knows how to cover Washington and, of course, elections,&quot; writes @JoeTrippi. But what if it isn't the right lens? &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/JohnJHarwood/status/1414746306652868611&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 13 Jul 2021 02:25:27 GMT" tweetId="1414772935953375235" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1414772935953375235" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="The editors at &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cleveland.com/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; (The Plain Dealer) decided they needed a new approach to &quot;covering political candidates who make false, irresponsible and potentially dangerous statements.&quot; Here's an update on how it's going. https://t.co/2c3cEjPCX7 https://t.co/tvvKx9mQkX" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 21:09:24 GMT" tweetId="1414693397835784197" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1414693397835784197" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Ominous sign. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.latimes.com/politics/story/2021-07-11/katie-porter-town-hall-irvine-scuffle&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 04:17:44 GMT" tweetId="1414438805319340035" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1414438805319340035" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 11" type="calendarDay" name="11" >
				<outline text="None of the networks that broadcast live today the âVirgin Galactic Launches Richard Branson Into Spaceâ story persuaded me that this was break-into-regular-programming news. The event remained at infomercial level." type="tweet" created="Sun, 11 Jul 2021 23:20:48 GMT" tweetId="1414364079951654912" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1414364079951654912" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Newspapers like the @LAtimes (and others) have been apologizing for their racist past. I recommend @BrentNYT's interpretation of what's going on with that. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/10/opinion/sunday/white-newspapers-african-americans.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/HPjqfYxfGw" type="tweet" created="Sun, 11 Jul 2021 18:37:24 GMT" tweetId="1414292756365824006" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1414292756365824006" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 10" type="calendarDay" name="10" >
				<outline text="&quot;As a paid product, though, itâs now part of a giant content muddle. If youâve decided youâre willing to pay for online news, why would you pick USA Today over the Post or Times â or over your local daily?&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.niemanlab.org/2021/07/usa-today-is-getting-a-paywall-whos-the-audience-for-it/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;

Indeed, why? I don't see the value proposition." type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 21:46:21 GMT" tweetId="1413977920452890629" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1413977920452890629" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Everyone can see how this toxic triangle operates. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.rollingstone.com/politics/politics-features/trump-mccarthy-republican-party-critical-race-theory-1184610/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/71y9XVv1xa" type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 18:35:33 GMT" tweetId="1413929903603519490" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1413929903603519490" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="When @propublica does an investigation and gets criticism from the people investigated, they don't just say, &quot;we stand by our story,&quot; or run a letter to the editor. They communicate with the complainants and respond point by point. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.propublica.org/article/sugar-companies-said-our-investigation-is-flawed-and-biased-lets-dive-into-why-thats-not-the-case&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; An excellent practice." type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 17:42:27 GMT" tweetId="1413916543742844928" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1413916543742844928" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="D.C. journalists launch media company with $10 million in funding. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.axios.com/dc-journalists-launch-media-company-ee38d5f8-0d45-490e-90c2-0cc1ba1036a7.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;

Good for them. But I can't tell what this is yet. Supposed to be &quot;a radically different publication, one that uses a distinct set of formats to deliver a nuanced and comprehensive view...&quot;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 16:52:44 GMT" tweetId="1413904030234030092" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1413904030234030092" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 9" type="calendarDay" name="09" >
				<outline text="Itâs likely you have never seen my typology of newspaper names. You might like it. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1317273282165559299&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 23:31:54 GMT" tweetId="1413642095349350401" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1413642095349350401" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="One of the more telling things I have read about the Washington press corps and what it prizes. The theme is coming down from the insane high of Trump to the sedate professionalism of the Biden White House.

In commenting on this they reveal themselves.  &lt;a href=&quot;https://ckarchive.com/b/k0umh6h0wo69&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 23:03:16 GMT" tweetId="1413634888515915777" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1413634888515915777" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="&quot;We perpetuated harmful stereotypes. We didnât take the time to understand the people we were writing about. We allowed this blindness to guide our words. It didnât serve our readers or our society.&quot;

&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.latimes.com/california/newsletter/2021-07-08/gwen-araujo-transgender-essential-california&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 20:44:47 GMT" tweetId="1413600039180644356" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1413600039180644356" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Two Harvard professors who spent more than twenty years studying the breakdown of democracies in Europe and Latin America conclude that &quot;the bulk of the Republican Party is behaving in an antidemocratic manner.&quot; Their latest warning in the @TheAtlantic.

&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2021/07/democracy-could-die-2024/619390/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 20:14:30 GMT" tweetId="1413592419887730694" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1413592419887730694" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Well, Susan, is there more violent crime now compared to 30 years ago? You're allowed to say. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/SusanPage/status/1413146886148554765&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 19:11:18 GMT" tweetId="1413576515762237446" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1413576515762237446" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Another way you know Fox is not a news network: At a news network, the claim 'NSA spies on a journalist, wants him off the air' would be treated as a major scoop (if true) and the newsroom would follow up, work the phones, try to confirm. At Fox it's, &quot;oh, that's Tucker's thing.&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/justinbaragona/status/1413169907777384449&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 15:10:03 GMT" tweetId="1413515800556736515" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1413515800556736515" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 8" type="calendarDay" name="08" >
				<outline text="Important if true. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/risj_oxford/status/1413279480399945729&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 23:38:35 GMT" tweetId="1413281388887937030" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1413281388887937030" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="I recommend @Edsall on a &quot;renegade segment of the electorate [that] welcomes authoritarian techniques to crush racial and cultural liberalism, seeks to wrest away the election machinery, and suffers from the mass delusion that Trump won last November.&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/07/opinion/trump-gop.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 18:56:56 GMT" tweetId="1413210510946971650" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1413210510946971650" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Today @cwarzel writes about &quot;hyperobjects&quot;â threats so large, and yet so gradual, that it makes a twisted kind of sense to do nothing about them, even though we can see the devastation to come. He says the &quot;normalcy bias&quot; in journalism makes it even worse. &lt;a href=&quot;https://warzel.substack.com/p/we-are-not-ready&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 16:32:57 GMT" tweetId="1413174275322822663" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1413174275322822663" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 7" type="calendarDay" name="07" >
				<outline text="&quot;Too unsafe to inhabit and too expensive to repair.&quot; Kinda like the GOP. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/BiancaJoanie/status/1412906321876295681&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 02:17:59 GMT" tweetId="1412959117057175562" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412959117057175562" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="&quot;Tucker Carlson sought Putin interview at time of spying claim.&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.axios.com/tucker-carlson-putin-interview-surveillance-c9952d7c-33d7-45e9-be68-2ba4c3817f98.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 01:53:08 GMT" tweetId="1412952861470863360" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412952861470863360" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="&quot;Ex-Rep. Vito Fossellaâs last-minute, game-changing endorsement from former President Donald Trump in the Staten Island borough president GOP primary got a paid, targeted Facebook boost from an unexpected source: conservative cable news outlet Newsmax.&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.thecity.nyc/2021/7/7/22567596/newsmax-facebook-trump-ad-fossella-staten-island-borough-president-win&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 01:23:27 GMT" tweetId="1412945390735962114" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412945390735962114" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Meanwhile,@ThePlumLineGS explains how Kevin McCarthy hath more to gain by trying to appoint crazies to the select committee investigating the events of January 6th. Recommended. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/theplumlinegs/status/1412903912231907333&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 23:13:25 GMT" tweetId="1412912667665305601" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412912667665305601" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Not just further to the right, but further from the real. Thatâs the direction the Party is moving in. 

Deadliest case: vaccination rates in the red states. Thereâs nothing inherently âconservativeâ (or pro-life) about being anti-vax.

But you can express your GOP-ness that way." type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 22:55:46 GMT" tweetId="1412908225230483458" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412908225230483458" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="I have been tracking this for years: the slow erosion of belief in what used to be newsroom objectivity. Excerpt from today's @CJR: It used to be her job to divorce herself from such emotions. That's how newsroom objectivity worked. Now she can flip it around: &quot;let it inform me.&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412855094375243778/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 19:24:38 GMT" tweetId="1412855094375243778" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412855094375243778" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="As a journalism professor myself, I cannot imagine having to declare about someone we actively recruited that we not only understand but SUPPORT her decision not to join our faculty because her treatment by our institution was racist. That would be crushing for the faculty body. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412797800929234948&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 16:28:50 GMT" tweetId="1412810850205933572" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412810850205933572" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="UNC J-faculty support @nhannahjones decision not to become their colleague. &quot;The appalling treatment of one of our nationâs most-decorated journalists by her own alma mater was humiliating, inappropriate, and unjust. We will be frank: It was racist.&quot;   &lt;a href=&quot;https://hussmanfaculty.medium.com/racism-and-reactionary-politics-kept-nikole-hannah-jones-from-joining-unc-54b947a4cb9c&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 15:36:58 GMT" tweetId="1412797800929234948" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412797800929234948" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="@JoekillianPW Hi, Joe. Forgive me if you have already done something on this. But did you see in a piece published Tuesday Walter Hussman's flat denials that he lobbied against a tenured appointment for @nhannahjones? &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.poynter.org/educators-students/2021/unc-donor-says-he-has-no-regrets-about-his-role-in-the-journalism-school-losing-nikole-hannah-jones/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 15:30:49 GMT" tweetId="1412796251213533187" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412796251213533187" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 6" type="calendarDay" name="06" >
				<outline text="What's a centrist? &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412567833691762692/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 00:23:10 GMT" tweetId="1412567833691762692" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412567833691762692" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="This interview with Walter Hussman Jr. says that after his gift to UNC he began talking to leading executives and journalism educators about his ideas. At one point he was going to challenge me to a debate about objectivity. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.poynter.org/educators-students/2021/unc-donor-says-he-has-no-regrets-about-his-role-in-the-journalism-school-losing-nikole-hannah-jones/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; First I am hearing of it." type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 00:18:01 GMT" tweetId="1412566537148448768" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412566537148448768" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Not only further to the right, but further from the real.

That's the direction the Republican Party is moving in. This report documents it better than any I have read. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/republican-trump-2022-midterms-election-falsehoods/2021/07/04/3a43438c-d36f-11eb-ae54-515e2f63d37d_story.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; Candidates equally &quot;conservative&quot; are losing to those who join in the Big Lie fantasy." type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 17:53:18 GMT" tweetId="1412469722348666881" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412469722348666881" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="At this point you have to ask how long the North Carolina J-school will be â can be â called Hussman.
&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.ncpolicywatch.com/2021/07/06/nikole-hannah-jones-declines-unc-tenure-offer-heads-to-howard-university/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/PnMNswKux0" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 15:29:51 GMT" tweetId="1412433618748772352" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412433618748772352" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="If you have been following the @nhannahjones fight, you have no choice but to read this thread. Combine it with her powerful statement &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.naacpldf.org/wp-content/uploads/NHJ-Statement-CBS-7.6.21-FINAL-8-am.pdf&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; and you know why she could not accept the job at UNC-Chapel Hil. https://t.co/pA9Ca5CTkn" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 15:01:43 GMT" tweetId="1412426540890181636" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412426540890181636" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="The site seems to be stalling from all the traffic. Try this link: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.naacpldf.org/wp-content/uploads/NHJ-Statement-CBS-7.6.21-FINAL-8-am.pdf&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/2ZRhpcE0fk" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 14:33:37 GMT" tweetId="1412419468211466241" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412419468211466241" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Please read the statement of @nhannahjones on why she turned down the appointment at University of North Carolina- Chapel Hill and took a (tenured) job at Howard University instead. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.naacpldf.org/press-release/nikole-hannah-jones-issues-statement-on-decision-to-decline-tenure-offer-at-university-of-north-carolina-chapel-hill-and-to-accept-knight-chair-appointment-at-howard-university/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 14:25:53 GMT" tweetId="1412417524327649290" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412417524327649290" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 5" type="calendarDay" name="05" >
				<outline text="Public service announcement. The Hill is not a news source. It's an SEO company attached to a right wing blog, and its owner is trying to sell it. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.axios.com/the-hill-nexstar-acquisition-e1906f1d-6b85-4219-8074-e5ae47e23155.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/ZhGC32wG5F" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 00:24:02 GMT" tweetId="1412205664898781186" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412205664898781186" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Further to the right doesnât capture it. The GOP is moving further from the real. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/brianstelter/status/1412160166108217347&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 05 Jul 2021 22:19:25 GMT" tweetId="1412174302246539265" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412174302246539265" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Reporters Without Borders (RSF) has published a &quot;gallery of grim portraits, those 37 heads of state or government who crack down massively on press freedom.&quot; New to the list of free press predators: MBS, Bolsonaro, OrbÃ¡n, Carrie Lam in Hong Kong. &lt;a href=&quot;https://rsf.org/en/news/rsfs-2021-press-freedom-predators-gallery-old-tyrants-two-women-and-european&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 05 Jul 2021 18:04:16 GMT" tweetId="1412110092191797259" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412110092191797259" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="I always go to the Times real estate section for examples of point-of-view journalism. In this little update â nothing special about it, run-of-the-mill report â it's a given that what we all want is for  apartment prices to go up. UP IS GOOD. Right? 1/3 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/02/realestate/manhattan-real-estate-sales.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 05 Jul 2021 17:22:56 GMT" tweetId="1412099691442065411" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412099691442065411" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" >
					<outline text="Here, for example, the good news is that people can finally make appointments to see apartments. Sales are up big time. The business is getting back to normal. This is good! One part is not so good, though. The damn things are less expensive. Boo. &quot;We&quot; hate that. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412099694491222021/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 05 Jul 2021 17:22:57 GMT" tweetId="1412099694491222021" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412099694491222021" inReplyToId="1412099691442065411" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" >
						<outline text="Optimism has returned. It's a new world. Except prices are still down. Terrible, isn't it?

Obviously this is news from the POV of the industry, and the owners and traders of &quot;luxury&quot; apartments. Which is fine. This section has always been that way.

Needs a better label, though. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412099698668752900/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 05 Jul 2021 17:22:58 GMT" tweetId="1412099698668752900" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412099698668752900" inReplyToId="1412099694491222021" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="&quot;Over the past nine months I have tried, with increasing bluntness, to get Rupert to understand the real damage that Fox News is doing to America. I failed, and it was arrogant and naÃ¯ve to ever have thought that I could succeed.&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.thedailybeast.com/former-murdoch-exec-says-fox-news-is-poison-for-america&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;

Indeed it was." type="tweet" created="Mon, 05 Jul 2021 16:28:08 GMT" tweetId="1412085900444672007" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1412085900444672007" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 4" type="calendarDay" name="04" >
				<outline text="You know those media bias charts that claim to arrange the major news providers from left to right leaning? I'd like to see one that tries to position popular news sources on a standards-of-verification axis. In other words, from most likely to be evidence-based to least likely. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1411778978436747266/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 04 Jul 2021 20:08:32 GMT" tweetId="1411778978436747266" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1411778978436747266" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Just a test. Only a test. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1411776513083650051/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 04 Jul 2021 19:58:44 GMT" tweetId="1411776513083650051" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1411776513083650051" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 3" type="calendarDay" name="03" >
				<outline text="Good weekend to sit down, brace yourself, and watch this. It is a superior act of reporting, with the simple goal of establishing what happened on Jan. 6th. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410698772418600965&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 03 Jul 2021 19:43:05 GMT" tweetId="1411410183541112836" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1411410183541112836" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 2" type="calendarDay" name="02" >
				<outline text="The sooner we start connecting the cooked books in the failed case for war during the W. Bush yearsâ¦ to âflood the zone with shitâ and 30,000 lies and misleading statements during the Trump yearsâ¦ the better off we will be in comprehending the Republican Party we have today. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/fmkaplan/status/1410606298157051916&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 21:39:57 GMT" tweetId="1411077209108926464" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1411077209108926464" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Beyond fact-checking lies a world where the events themselves are false. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/tackettdc/status/1411008716439175168&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 18:14:25 GMT" tweetId="1411025481814654977" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1411025481814654977" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="@willwilkinson This was good, Will. &lt;a href=&quot;https://modelcitizen.substack.com/p/q-trust-and-you&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 17:15:54 GMT" tweetId="1411010757773365250" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1411010757773365250" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="I have met Times people in that room. Even an outsider can surmise that its value to the organization is... high. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/marclacey/status/1410765744044969993&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 16:06:28 GMT" tweetId="1410993285489954819" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410993285489954819" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 1" type="calendarDay" name="01" >
				<outline text="&quot;On some issues in some eras, journalists should become outright activists,&quot; writes @dangillmor. 

On his list: for constitutional government, &quot;public grounding in reality,&quot; more level playing fields, freedom of expression, and action on climate change. &lt;a href=&quot;https://dangillmor.medium.com/dear-journalists-please-declare-independence-from-business-as-usual-fe8d3681f932&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 02:57:00 GMT" tweetId="1410794609509343233" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410794609509343233" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" >
					<outline text="Five years ago I wrote a post similar to Dan's: &quot;Things I think journalists are allowed to advocate for in covering an election.&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://pressthink.org/2016/10/campaign-press-not-neutral-toward/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; On my list: pro-participation, pro-verification, pro-deliberation, pro-accountability, against opacity, against demagoguery." type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 02:57:01 GMT" tweetId="1410794610947919878" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410794610947919878" inReplyToId="1410794609509343233" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="When the University of North Carolina- Chapel Hill finally did, under pressure, grant tenure to @nhannahjones, it was a victory, yes, but in &quot;a battle that shouldnât have needed fighting,&quot; writes @KarenAttiah. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/2021/07/01/nikole-hannah-jones-tenure-victory-unc/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;

Hers is the right way to see it." type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 01:33:07 GMT" tweetId="1410773498931384320" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410773498931384320" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Rage watching is easy. Rage writing is not easyâ to do well. This is a masterful example. 

Sally Jenkins of the Washington Post rips into the NFL's handling of its investigation into a culture of sexual harassment at the team once known as the Redskins. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.washingtonpost.com/sports/2021/07/01/washington-football-team-dan-snyder-sally-jenkins/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 00:52:37 GMT" tweetId="1410763304633618432" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410763304633618432" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Six months of investigation went into this: &quot;Day of Rage: An In-Depth Look at How a Mob Stormed the Capitol.&quot; An outstanding work of journalism and forensics. For the first time I have a grasp of the whole.  &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/video/us/politics/100000007606996/capitol-riot-trump-supporters.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; 

And not a single &quot;both sides&quot; note is struck." type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 20:36:11 GMT" tweetId="1410698772418600965" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410698772418600965" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Best sentence I read yesterday.

&quot;Rumsfeld started being wrong within hours of the attacks and never stopped.&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2021/06/how-donald-rumsfeld-deserves-be-remembered/619334/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 17:08:45 GMT" tweetId="1410646568936615940" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410646568936615940" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="There should be a term for that state of human affairs when an event happens, there is public interest in it, people want information â  they want to consume news â but there is no news to be had because it is simply too early in the event, and what fills the vacuum is... crappy." type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 14:47:04 GMT" tweetId="1410610913367920661" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410610913367920661" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="The research program I direct, @membershippzzle, is sunsetting in August. But first we're having a big event to sum up the state of membership models in news. It's online, for 2-3 hours a day, August 2-6. Hundreds already signed up across the globe. Program is taking shape too. https://t.co/5rmR8zP0op" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 14:15:52 GMT" tweetId="1410603063677657088" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410603063677657088" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="&quot;Rumsfeld started being wrong within hours of the attacks and never stopped.&quot; https://t.co/pGv2mNmuaN

Recommended obituary." type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 05:07:04 GMT" tweetId="1410464950859010048" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410464950859010048" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="If you missed it.

&quot;Trustees for the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill voted Wednesday afternoon at a closed session to give tenure to star New York Times writer Nikole Hannah-Jones several months after refusing to consider her proposed tenure.&quot; https://t.co/UuR0lgGEMh" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 04:25:34 GMT" tweetId="1410454510108041217" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410454510108041217" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			</outline>
		<outline text="June 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="june2021" >
			<outline text="June 30" type="calendarDay" name="30" >
				<outline text="When it came down to the Board of Trustees being held accountable for their votes, different story. Congratulations to @nhannahjones, tenured professor. https://t.co/OM77Y7BxN9" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 22:11:03 GMT" tweetId="1410360260251078665" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410360260251078665" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Not only further to the right, but further from the real.

That's the direction in which the Republican Party is moving. Here's a report from Michigan. https://t.co/o7mjIkbuud Republican official who checked into fraud claims in the election, found none, and isn't believed." type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 20:58:47 GMT" tweetId="1410342071551004674" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410342071551004674" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="One way you know Fox is not a news network is that when Carlson makes a wild â but important-if-true â factual claim, the so-called &quot;news side&quot; doesn't confirm it, refute it, or even tell you they're working on it. A news network would not act like that. https://t.co/3Rn1e3tGxS" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 14:51:51 GMT" tweetId="1410249730395979776" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410249730395979776" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Why cover Tucker? 

@brianstelter: &quot;He hosts the single biggest gathering of GOP diehards anywhere on TV... the rest of us have to decide: Ignore what he spews, or scrutinize it and supply a reality check, knowing that's going to cause him to double down?&quot; https://t.co/JK39pIU0Vp" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 13:57:24 GMT" tweetId="1410236027327893507" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410236027327893507" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 29" type="calendarDay" name="29" >
				<outline text="Itâs a two-party system and one party is increasingly anti-democratic. The direction the GOP travels is not only further to the right, but further from the real. Put âem together - the drift away from democracy, away from reality - and the conflict with journalism is structural." type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 21:58:44 GMT" tweetId="1409994769808429063" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409994769808429063" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="I would not sign on to this: &quot;Focusing on the supply problem is a waste of energy and resources.&quot; But I agree  that we often focus on the supply side of disinformation because the demand side is hellacious, depressing, confounding, and it makes you weep for this country. https://t.co/WSjDNVWLQG" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 19:22:20 GMT" tweetId="1409955412724625413" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409955412724625413" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Yes. Her name is @Yamiche https://t.co/WBJyD8VKsx" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 18:59:06 GMT" tweetId="1409949566540161031" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409949566540161031" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="The top 20 NPR-affiliated public radio stations had on average a total weekly listenership of about 9 million in 2020, down 9% from 2019.
 
In 2020, the NewsHour on PBS attracted 1.2 million viewers on average, up 18% from the year before. https://t.co/yCZNnl8mKd" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 18:51:49 GMT" tweetId="1409947730642886664" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409947730642886664" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="&quot;Opposition media traditionally relies on traffic booms when a new party takes office, but right-wing outlets have seen some of the most precipitous declines in readership since a Democratic president took office.&quot; https://t.co/i6U0EwlM9A" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 16:13:09 GMT" tweetId="1409907802789789702" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409907802789789702" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 28" type="calendarDay" name="28" >
				<outline text="The New York Times now allows subscribers to âgiftâ articles to people who don't subscribe. The gifted articles wonât count towards the limited number of links that non-subscribers can click before hitting a paywall. Recipients have 14 days to read them. https://t.co/SpWBjaP4eH" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 02:19:22 GMT" tweetId="1409697972581933066" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409697972581933066" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="For 35 years I'm on the journalism faculty at NYU. We taught First Amendment. Times vs. Sullivan. Pentagon Papers. Inverted pyramid. (Google it.)

We taught &quot;Frank Sinatra has a cold.&quot; Google it!

We didn't teach: We have a two party system and one of the two is anti-democratic." type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 23:25:50 GMT" tweetId="1409654302239383554" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409654302239383554" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Alright. Letâs see what you got, Trustees. https://t.co/jBDrzMTkqt" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 22:19:08 GMT" tweetId="1409637518807420935" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409637518807420935" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Heâs right . You should read it. https://t.co/MOdNkbcWCB" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 22:02:04 GMT" tweetId="1409633223999586306" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409633223999586306" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="This is a great start. Next step: A link to a longer &quot;here's where I'm coming from&quot; page with personal background, any important disclosures, and other view-from-somewhere information. Scroll down on this page to see what I mean. https://t.co/1qoPQlM6rx https://t.co/NbW14CF3fW" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 19:08:59 GMT" tweetId="1409589664910962690" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409589664910962690" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="&quot;The UNC-Chapel Hill Board of Trustees will vote on tenure for Nikole Hannah-Jones this week...&quot; https://t.co/lxjKbleRSM

This is good. Now board members have to emerge from behind the screen of procedure and take a clear stand. Good on @nhannahjones for pressing forward." type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 17:12:14 GMT" tweetId="1409560284734406656" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409560284734406656" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="What's different about this piece is that it frames the campaign to flood the zone with shit (in order to undermine the possibility that Americans can share a common set of facts...) as a national security threat. https://t.co/ipVKkGqL8a Recommended." type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 16:38:58 GMT" tweetId="1409551911964004358" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409551911964004358" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Read this man's plea. https://t.co/FjIQL1lQJ2" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 15:51:23 GMT" tweetId="1409539937133903876" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409539937133903876" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 27" type="calendarDay" name="27" >
				<outline text="This is a headline live on the @USAToday site now. https://t.co/LkW9tVp1gV Via @_cingraham https://t.co/ikQKUZHtn1" type="tweet" created="Sun, 27 Jun 2021 23:02:40 GMT" tweetId="1409286084895383554" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409286084895383554" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" >
					<outline text="They changed it. https://t.co/Qj6CuuUq6S" type="tweet" created="Sun, 27 Jun 2021 23:51:43 GMT" tweetId="1409298427968733184" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409298427968733184" inReplyToId="1409286084895383554" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Exactly. All in. Which is why measures stronger than fact-checking are needed from journalists. Examples include: Denial of platform. Relentlessly reminding the public what office-holders did on Jan. 6 or to further the Big Lie. Aggressive questioning that never folds or forgets. https://t.co/dpKYDKgzXa" type="tweet" created="Sun, 27 Jun 2021 22:44:44 GMT" tweetId="1409281570352074755" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409281570352074755" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Tim Lambert is the speaker. Multimedia News Director and Morning Edition host at WITF, the NPR station in Harrisburg, PA. @nprpolitics could follow its local affiliate's lead in accountability reporting https://t.co/2Q4uP93a97 but it has not done so. WITF is out there on its own. https://t.co/yIhj0nwQb2" type="tweet" created="Sun, 27 Jun 2021 20:40:25 GMT" tweetId="1409250287588679681" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409250287588679681" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="&quot;How Wikipedia deals with the lab leak theory may seem trivial. After all, practically every major newspaper, website [and] ex-late night TV host has wrangled with it in the past few months. But there's something uniquely powerful about Wikipedia.&quot; https://t.co/y8SWnk84uJ" type="tweet" created="Sun, 27 Jun 2021 18:59:07 GMT" tweetId="1409224793069604864" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409224793069604864" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="If you have been meaning to inform yourself about the lab leak hypothesis, but were waiting for the right explainer that would lay out the facts minus the ideological warfare, here you go. https://t.co/GzNArbUq5C By @zeynep in her best &quot;what we know/what we don't know&quot; style." type="tweet" created="Sun, 27 Jun 2021 17:16:03 GMT" tweetId="1409198854352875524" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409198854352875524" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 26" type="calendarDay" name="26" >
				<outline text="I listened. It was hard to tell exactly what they have in mind, but... Their vision for @LATimes mixes an entertainment company, cultural institution, modern day agora, and powerhouse newsroom into a giant engagement engine for news, culture and community. To which you subscribe. https://t.co/FhSs1VI3gR" type="tweet" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2021 17:09:59 GMT" tweetId="1408834941895548934" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408834941895548934" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="It's there in a Reuters report from Thursday: the importance to Democrats of the two-tracks. https://t.co/wm65yoAM0l 

Move to Friday's AP report. Senators were described as âflooredâ and âfrustratedâ by Biden's insistence on the two track approach. Why did the AP do that? 1/2 https://t.co/LSfrdXP9z4" type="tweet" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2021 16:26:13 GMT" tweetId="1408823928454328324" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408823928454328324" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" >
					<outline text="Here's the AP: &quot;Bidenâs bipartisan infrastructure deal was thrown in doubt Friday as Republican senators felt 'blindsided' by his insistence that it must move in tandem with his bigger package.&quot; https://t.co/1PhLSHt4ao

Again: Why did @AP buy the &quot;we were blindsided&quot; gambit? 2/2" type="tweet" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2021 16:26:14 GMT" tweetId="1408823930706616325" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408823930706616325" inReplyToId="1408823928454328324" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 25" type="calendarDay" name="25" >
				<outline text="Quote from @Edsall (@ Washington Post for 25 years):

&quot;During times of big change reporters have a harder time [than academics do] finding ways both to describe it and to deal with it. Reporters are usually fixed in a language that they've been using...&quot; https://t.co/gxPZrjFieI" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 22:07:52 GMT" tweetId="1408547518229647369" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408547518229647369" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Among the people who &quot;don't know any better&quot; are reporters and editors at CNN. https://t.co/BcYav90Aah https://t.co/2uifS3hUMt" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 19:21:43 GMT" tweetId="1408505703958990848" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408505703958990848" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="You could see this coming. 

&quot;Republican senators Friday were frantically considering options as the future of the sweeping compromise appeared in doubt... Senators were described as 'stunned,' 'floored' and 'frustrated.'&quot; https://t.co/1PhLSHt4ao https://t.co/bmMaUQhEm3" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 18:46:13 GMT" tweetId="1408496771047772164" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408496771047772164" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="If you need a summary of where the @nhannahjones appointment at UNC-Chapel Hill stands, @CJR has a good one today. https://t.co/AzDTBokWjf This is a story I am following closely." type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 18:25:19 GMT" tweetId="1408491512154017798" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408491512154017798" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="The valence of this observation (&quot;more a kind of media platform...&quot;) has only increased since March. https://t.co/VyqCmVa79G" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 17:26:24 GMT" tweetId="1408476684895019012" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408476684895019012" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="The âsharia law&quot; comparison seems right to me. https://t.co/X2AbdQxT44 I'd add that the mania to root out Critical Race Theory (without knowing what it is) is an attempt at symbolic reversal of the multi-racial coalition found marching in the streets after George Floyd's murder. https://t.co/7CEXZGgSI6" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 16:34:02 GMT" tweetId="1408463504798007297" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408463504798007297" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="I will listen to this when I get the time. Patrick Soon-Shiong (wealthy owner, immigrant, self-made, biotech) and Kevin Merida (new editor, African-American, print and digital DNA) are an intriguing combination. They could come up with something different. https://t.co/FhSs1VI3gR" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 16:00:21 GMT" tweetId="1408455028302651394" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408455028302651394" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Good morning. Can someone explain to me why the Washington Post is reporting that five Republicans in the Senate have signed on to Biden's infrastructure proposal https://t.co/aO1lY8XWSl while USA Today is saying it's 21 Senators with 11 Republicans? https://t.co/S8nPJ5zDCA" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:29:09 GMT" tweetId="1408447178465550336" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408447178465550336" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 24" type="calendarDay" name="24" >
				<outline text="How do five Republican votes for an infrastucture plan become ten when getting ten will trigger passage via reconciliation of a huge economic package those same Republicans do not want? And that's before we factor in the Green Lanternism of anything the press calls  &quot;bipartisan.&quot;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 01:58:18 GMT" tweetId="1408243120278585345" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408243120278585345" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Small sign but a good one. @nytimes hired a technology reporter whose beat will not be tech, but specifically tech accountability. https://t.co/9gDW1jUT6M Congrats @RMac18" type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 20:53:42 GMT" tweetId="1408166467129036804" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408166467129036804" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="When this event passes through the looking glass in the other direction and is presented as &quot;news,&quot; it will be a test of what journalism has learned about reporting on disinformation. https://t.co/zhlxUM5u3w" type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 19:33:12 GMT" tweetId="1408146208951091203" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408146208951091203" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="&quot;The past is never dead. It's not even past.&quot; The fight over the @nhannahjones appointment shows how true that is. Read this:

&quot;The White press helped destroy democracy in the South. Black journalists developed an activist tradition because they had to.&quot; https://t.co/jTl7WZnC7q" type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 17:59:16 GMT" tweetId="1408122569601990661" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408122569601990661" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="If we could give the entire file of Trump coverage grades, there would be some As, Bs, Cs, Ds, and Fs for different streams in it. For the Ivanka &amp;amp; Jared portion, a grade of F isn't enough. You would have to attach a note, &quot;please come see me about Billy's work.&quot;

What a fiasco. https://t.co/BcYav90Aah" type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 14:39:29 GMT" tweetId="1408072290596790273" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408072290596790273" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			</outline>
		</body>
	</opml>
